               <head>Work on Sufism</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Javāmiʿ al-hidāyat by Sayyid Faz̤l Allāh Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad al-Ḥusaynī al-Kālpavī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_985-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7528">Sayyid Faz̤l Allāh Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad al-Ḥusaynī al-Kālpavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7528">سيّد فضل الله احمد ابن محمّد الحسينى الكالپوى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21811">Javāmiʿ al-hidāyat</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21811">جوامع الهدايت</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on the doctrines and principles of Sufism by <persName key="person_f7528" role="aut">Sayyid Faz̤l Allāh Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad al-Ḥusaynī of Kalpi (Malwa)</persName>, based on other Ṣūfī works and the teachings of <persName key="person_f7300" role="ant">Mīr Sayyid Abū Saʿīd</persName> and his grandfather, <persName key="person_f7301" role="ant">Mīr Sayyid Aḥmad ibn Mīr Sayyid Muḥammad</persName>, transmitted in gatherings and discussions. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work was written at the request of his two masters and completed, according to a chronogram at the end, in 1107/1695-6. 
</p>
                        <p>The work is divided into eighty-two chapters, each termed hidāyat or guidance. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 120v): completed 1210/1795-6. A further note states the work was checked against the original and mistakes were corrected. 
</p>
                        <p>Parts of the volume are annotated by the son of <persName key="person_f7547" role="oth">Shāh Barkat Allāh Qādirī</persName> according to a note at the beginning (f. 1r). 
                        </p>
                        <p>This volume was copied by at least two nastaʿlīq hands ranging in size. 
</p>
                        <p>Bound folios, but lacking original binding; torn sheet of advertisements (dated August 3, 1871) as cover. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
